aquamarine:   Aquamarine
aquamarine:
aquamarine: Aquamarine is a very light linux rendering backend library. It provides
aquamarine: basic abstractions for an application to render on a Wayland session
aquamarine: (in a window) or a native DRM session.
aquamarine: It is agnostic of the rendering API (Vulkan/OpenGL) and designed to be
aquamarine: lightweight, performant, and minimal.
aquamarine: Aquamarine provides no bindings for other languages. It is C++-only.
aquamarine:
aquamarine: https://github.com/hyprwm/aquamarine
aquamarine:
